snippet.textDisplay:
If you've read many Batman comics then you know that Bruce Wayne watching his parents die before him was just the beginning of his tramtic life. To use the "tip if the iceberg" metaphor. On the surface. Above the water. Most people just see a rich orphan with a strange coping mechanism. When his parents' deaths are the bottom tip of the iceberg. Buried below so many years of trauma and turmoil. I love how the iceberg metaphor works so well for Batman. When you do see an iceberg. You know to be afraid. You don't know just how deep it goes.
A man who has witnessed, felt, been shaped by so much fear and pain. Then using ALL of that. Rising above the mire. Making himself FEAR. A man so intelliegent. So skilled. So much iron will. Using every bit of it to become the boogyman against the boogyman. One that even Superman knows there are many reasons to be afraid of him. I LOVE that!
